The White House will be hosting its fourth annual Halloween festivities on October 25, 2020. The event is open to frontline workers, military families, and schoolchildren accompanied by their parents. Precautions have been put in place to ensure the health and safety of all attendees. The President and First Lady will greet trick-or-treaters, and various departments and agencies will be present with fun activities for children. Some highlights include space-related items from NASA, a visit from Smokey the Bear, photo opportunities with backdrops from the Department of Labor and the Department of Education, and model rockets on display from the Department of Transportation. The United States Air Force Strolling Strings will provide music for the festivities. Certain items are not allowed on the White House grounds, and attendees can call a 24-hour information line for event updates.